Author: kajecounterhack
Content: Quote [Wikipedia]: An ibex, commonly called by its French name: bouquetin also called steinbock in German[citation needed], is a type of wild mountain goat with large recurved horns that are transversely ridged in front. Ibex are found in Eurasia, North Africa, and East Africa. The name ibex comes from Latin, borrowed from Iberian or Aquitanian, akin to Old Spanish bezerro "bull", modern Spanish becerro "yearling". Ranging in height from 27 to 43 inches and weighing 200 to 270 pounds (90 to 120 kg), the ibex can live 20 years.

Author: sutro
Content: From the elegant simplicity of its site design to the game-changing nature of its burger-meets-hotdog product offering, it's easy to see why Burger Pipe has become the darling of the TechCrunch 50000. BurgerPipe.com's understated use of navigational system beeps alone has already created massive economic synergies. Yahoo, Microsoft, Facebook, and Xobni are all pretenders to the throne. At the end of the day, there's only one Google-killer, and it happens to be a burger in the shape of a pipe.
